TITLE: Using Block with Proper Overrides (Correct Approach)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates the correct way to extend Block with additional CSS properties by using the overrides prop. This approach properly applies custom styles that aren't part of the Block API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uber/baseweb/blob/main/documentation-site/pages/guides/styling.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import * as React from "react";
import { Block } from "baseui/block";

export default function Widget({ children }) {
  return (
    <Block
      backgroundColor="backgroundPrimary"
      color="contentPrimary"
      overrides={{
        Block: {
          style: { pointerEvents: "none" },
        },
      }}
    >
      {children}
    </Block>
  );
}
```

