TITLE: Testing Drag and Drop with Playwright in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to write end-to-end tests for drag and drop functionality using Playwright. Includes examples for both mouse-based and keyboard-based interactions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uber/baseweb/blob/main/documentation-site/pages/blog/drag-and-drop-list/index.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
test("dnd the first item to second position", async () => {
  await page.mouse.move(190, 111);
  await page.mouse.down();
  await page.mouse.move(190, 190);
  await page.mouse.up();
  expect(await getListItems(page)).toEqual([
    "Item 2",
    "Item 1",
    "Item 3",
    "Item 4",
    "Item 5",
    "Item 6",
  ]);
});
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
test("move the first item to second position", async () => {
  await page.keyboard.press("Tab");
  await page.keyboard.press("Space");
  await page.keyboard.press("ArrowDown");
  await page.keyboard.press("Space");
  expect(await getListItems(page)).toEqual([
    "Item 2",
    "Item 1",
    "Item 3",
    "Item 4",
    "Item 5",
    "Item 6",
  ]);
});
```

