TITLE: Themed Styling with createThemedUseStyletron Hook in Base Web
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use `createThemedUseStyletron` to create a themed version of the `useStyletron` hook. It defines a custom theme type `CustomTheme` and uses it to create a themed `useStyletron` hook that provides access to the custom theme's properties. This approach simplifies styling components with custom themes using the `useStyletron` hook.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uber/baseweb/blob/main/documentation-site/pages/blog/base-web-v8/index.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { createThemedUseStyletron } from "baseui";

type CustomTheme = { customColor: string };

const themedUseStyletron =
  createThemedUseStyletron<CustomTheme>();

function ComponentA() {
  const [css, theme] = themedUseStyletron();
  return (
    <div className={css({ color: theme.customColor })}>
      test
    </div>
  );
}
```

