TITLE: Customizing Theme Primitives in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to customize the theme primitives to use blue as the primary color instead of the new default black in Base Web v9.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uber/baseweb/blob/main/documentation-site/pages/blog/base-web-v9/index.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { createTheme, lightThemePrimitives } from "baseui/themes";
import { colors } from "baseui/tokens";

const myThemePrimitives = {
  ...lightThemePrimitives,
  primary: colors.blue400,
  primary50: colors.blue50,
  primary100: colors.blue100,
  primary200: colors.blue200,
  primary300: colors.blue300,
  primary400: colors.blue400,
  primary500: colors.blue500,
  primary600: colors.blue600,
  primary700: colors.blue700,
};

const myTheme = createTheme(myThemePrimitives);

export default myTheme;
```

