TITLE: Implementing a Reusable Widget with useStyletron (Incorrect Approach)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates an incorrect way to create a reusable component with useStyletron by concatenating class names. This approach leads to non-deduped CSS and potential issues with style application order when using the atomic Styletron engine.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uber/baseweb/blob/main/documentation-site/pages/guides/styling.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import * as React from "react";
import { useStyletron } from "baseui";

export default function Widget({ style, ...props }) {
  const [css] = useStyletron();
  return (
    <div
      {...props}
      className={[
        css({
          display: "flex",
          alignItems: "center",
          justifyContent: "center",
        }),
        css(style),
      ].join(" ")}
    />
  );
}
```

